# Project Architecture

## Folder structure

- `config/` — app-specific configuration (feed sources, keywords). Suffix: `.config.ts`
- `services/` — API communication and data fetching. Suffix: `.service.ts`
- `utils/` — pure, reusable functions (no React, no side effects). Suffix: `.util.ts`
- `hooks/` — custom React hooks grouped by logical domain. Suffix: `.hooks.ts`
- `contexts/` — React Context providers + consumer hooks. Suffix: `Context.tsx`
- `types/` — shared TypeScript interfaces and type definitions

## Components (Atomic Design)

- `atoms/` — smallest building blocks (SkeletonPulse, SentimentBar, ErrorDisplay)
- `molecules/` — compositions of atoms (ArticleSlider, FeaturedSection, DaySummary)
- `organisms/` — full sections with business logic (CategorySection, CategoryFeed, AppHeader)
- `pages/` — top-level page components (FeedPage)

## Key rules

- No `.find()` or `.filter()` calls in components — extract to utils or hooks
- No prop drilling — use Context + custom hooks for shared state
- Services return typed result objects (not thrown exceptions)
- Error handling uses `AppError` discriminated union from `types/errors.ts`
